The '''Nova Core''' was an organization within the [[Bureau of Scouting and Exploration Services]] that rewarded outstanding [[Scout/Legends|scouts]]. Each scout inducted into the Nova Core had at least two [[Standard year/Legends|years]] working in the Scout Service, and had visited at least five new [[Planet/Legends|planets]]. Entry requirements were strict; prospective candidates had to be nominated by an existing Nova member, and there was a limit of four beings per [[Sector/Legends|sector]] who could be inducted. Nova Core maintained a Scout "Hall of Fame" honoring deceased scouts. [[Talek Var]] was the youngest inductee, and also the first to be inducted posthumously. [[Burt Jaxton]] was a retired Nova scout,<ref name="GG8">''[[Galaxy Guide 8: Scouts]]''</ref> and [[Ecclesis von der Agar]] was a decorated but befuddled member.<ref name="G9">{{GamerCite|9|Endor and the Moddell Sector}}</ref>

